This is a missed-optimization in InstCombine.

The following program reveals the missed optimization.
The source program is
```llvm
define i1 @trunc_equality_bool(i8 %a, i8 %b) {
  %at = trunc nuw i8 %a to i1
  %bt = trunc nuw i8 %b to i1
  %eq = icmp eq i1 %at, %bt
  ret i1 %eq
}

```

However, current LLVM cannot optimize the source program. The expected optimized program is
```llvm
define i1 @trunc_equality_bool(i8 %a, i8 %b) {
  %eq = icmp eq i8 %a, %b
  ret i1 %eq
}

```
Please modify the following code in llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCompares.cpp:InstCombinerImpl::visitICmpInst to implement the missed optimization:
